==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/mi:li/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːli|-iːli]]

===Etymology===
See [[meal]]

====Adjective====
'''mealy'''
# Describing a substance, especially a dry [[foodstuff]] such as grain, that resembles [[meal]]. "Below the hole the mice made in the [[woodwork]] was a pile of ''mealy'' [[sawdust]]."

===Compound words===
*'''mealy-mouthed''': (adj) speaking disengenuously or with purposeful vagueness, as, metaphorically, speaking indistinctly with a mouthful of meal to confuse the listener; lying.  "What a mealy-mouthed politician!"

